==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sirenia
<hw>Si*re"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of large aquatic herbivorous mammals,
including the manatee, dugong, rytina, and several fossil
genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The hind limbs are either rudimentary or wanting, and
the front ones are changed to paddles. They have horny plates on the
front part of the jaws, and usually flat-crowned molar teeth. The
stomach is complex and the intestine long, as in other herbivorous
mammals. See <er>Cetacea</er> <sd>(b)</sd>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sirenian</ent>⟦br⟧
